text: Euryomma muisca is a species of fly in the genus Euryomma. It was first described by Grisales et al. in 2012. == Etymology == Euryomma muisca is named after the Muisca, who inhabited the central highlands (Altiplano Cundiboyacense) of present-day Colombia where the fly has been found. == Description == The fly has dark brown frontal vitta, the length of the postpedicel is 1.5 times the length of the pedicel. The wings are approximately long. == See also == *List of flora and fauna named after the Muisca == References == == Bibliography == * * Category:Fanniidae Category:Diptera of South America Category:Arthropods of Colombia Category:Endemic fauna of Colombia Category:Altiplano Cundiboyacense Muisca Category:Insects described in 2012
